comment_text: PCs were peaking 10-15 years ago. In the 90s and early 2000s, each upgrade you did every year was exciting, as it brought big improvements. As a 90s kid, I HAD TO upgrade my PC every year. It was pretty much mandatory, the difference was so big, and a 2 year old PC was really obsolete. But in the 2010s and today, using a 10 year old PC causes no issues whatsoever. Laptops followed shortly after. The same thing is happening with smartphones. In the 10 years after iPhone was released, every year brough exciting upgrades on all platforms. Phones became much faster, look much nicer, have much better screen, etc... But they peaked ~5 years ago. Their screen is near perfect, they perform all task instantaneously, so there is nothing really to improve. I often accidentally grab my 5yo Xs instead of 15 Pro, and only notice when I try to call someone and there is no service on it:D
